Title: zzz - Typewritten description of photograph of James B. Shackelford and George Dromgold on the S.S. Monterey, 1933
Description.caption: Text from nitrate negative sleeve: Shackleford, James B., Naturalist, 1933
Description.note: Text reads: Frank B. Howe, Room 962, 1150 So. Broadway, Los Angeles, Calif.  Gratis.  Mention of ship name is requested.  James B. Shackelford, who achieved world fame when he spent five years in the Gobi desert with Roy Chapman Andrews and made the dinosaur egg discovery, is back from another adventure.  Arriving in America on the SS Monterey, he comes this time from a year in the cannibal country of New Guinea with George Dromgold where the two took 50,000 feet of movies of life never before pictured.  They had a cannibal boat crew as their sole companions.  The picture shows Shackelford (right) and Dromgold on the Monterey as they returned.
Description.fundingNote: Access to this collection is generously supported by Arcadia funds.
